iller’s psychology and his plays. Concentrating largely on Miller’s most prolific decades of the 1940s, 1950s, and 1960s, Lahr probes Miller’s early playwriting failures; his work writing radio plays during World War II after being rejected for military service; his only novel, Focus; and his succession of award-winning and canonical plays that include All My Sons, Death of a Salesman, and The Crucible, providing an original interpretation of Miller’s work and his personality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDramatists, Americany20th centuryvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300268768?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300268768423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300268768/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY